-- Kerviel guilty of computer abuse, forgery: court
-- 
-- Tue Oct 5, 2010 4:56am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/10/05/us-socgen-kerviel-abuse-idUSTRE69417V20101005

 

 PARIS  (Reuters) - Former Societe Generale trader Jerome Kerviel was found guilty of computer abuse and forgery by a Paris court on Tuesday relating to his role in a trading scandal that cost the bank close to 5 billion euros ($7 billion). 

 "Kerviel knowingly went beyond his remit as a trader," presiding judge Dominique Pauthe told the court. ($1=.7296 Euro) (Reporting by Lionel Laurent; Editing by  James Regan )